The Job Log shows the jobs and ranks you have taken so far. It's also the universal widget for jobs such as Trapper (it sets traps).

Alright. You need to know a few things:

Every job has three ranks: Apprentice (L1), Journeyman (L2), and Master (L3). Higher ranks give you better chances of completing the related tasks. The rank names can vary a bit.

You get 3 + level (no ECL) Job Points, capped at 30 Job Points. You can spend these Job Points on 'buying' jobs and ranks.

L1 rank costs 3 Job Points, L2 costs 6 pts, and L3 costs 9 pts. So, if you go from L2 to L3 you pay 9 Job Points. This means you can only reach one job at Master level, as you need 18 Job Points for the three ranks together, and you'll get 30 at most.

In general you can attempt to do a task (for example refining ore) without having the relevant job (Refiner), but you'll get a high chance of failing. Taking the 1st level of Refining increases the chance of success., and higher ranks get even more increases and the chance of finding more ore.

Look on the forums for a list of Jobs and their rank benefits.
